Package org.wildfly.security.keystore

Class ModifyTrackingKeyStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.security.KeyStore
      • org.wildfly.security.keystore.ModifyTrackingKeyStore
  • public class ModifyTrackingKeyStore
extends java.security.KeyStore
    A KeyStore implementation that tracks if it's contents have been modified through the API since the last load / save.
    Author:
    Darran Lofthouse

      • modifyTrackingKeyStore

        public static ModifyTrackingKeyStore modifyTrackingKeyStore​(java.security.KeyStore toWrap)
                                                     throws java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException,
                                                            java.security.cert.CertificateException,
                                                            java.io.IOException
        Wrap an existing initialised KeyStore with a wrapper to track if it is modified.
        Parameters:
        toWrap - the KeyStore to wrap
        Returns:
        the wrapper around the KeyStore
        Throws:
        java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException - if the keystore could not be loaded due to a missing algorithm
        java.security.cert.CertificateException - if the keystore could not be loaded due to a certificate problem
        java.io.IOException - if the keystore could not be loaded due to an I/O problem
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the KeyStore being wrapped is null

      • isModified

        public boolean isModified()
        Identify if the KeyStore has been modified through this implementation since the last call to save or load.
        Returns:
        true if the KeyStore has been modified, false otherwise.
